        <abstract>
            <p>Emma and Leonard have scarlet fever.</p> 
<p><hi rend="italic">Houstonia</hi> seems "a grand case"; J. T. Rothrock should publish his observations on the two pollens and the reciprocal action of two hermaphrodites.</p>  
<p><hi rend="italic">Rhexia glandulosa</hi> offers nothing odd, but <hi rend="italic">Heterocentron</hi> will turn out something marvellous like <hi rend="italic">Lythrum</hi>.</p>  
<p>Would like to know what AG thinks of last chapter of <hi rend="italic">Orchids</hi>.</p> 
        </abstract>
